  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are good, low-cost (or free) alternatives to Google Alerts?",
  "response": "There are several low-cost or free alternatives to Google Alerts that can help you monitor online mentions of specific keywords, track news, or stay updated on topics of interest. Some of these alternatives include:\n\n1. **Talkwalker Alerts**: This is a free service that offers similar functionality to Google Alerts, allowing you to track mentions of keywords across the web, including news sites, blogs, forums, and social media.\n\n2. **Mention**: This tool offers a free plan with limited mentions, allowing users to track online references for specific keywords. While more advanced features come with paid plans, the free version can be sufficient for basic monitoring.\n\n3. **Feedly**: Although primarily a news reader, Feedly can be used to create keyword alerts. By setting up feeds with specific keywords, you can have relevant articles delivered to your Feedly account.\n\n4. **Social Searcher**: Social Searcher has a free version that allows users to track mentions on social media platforms like Facebook, Twitter, and Instagram. It provides key insights and analytics related to your search terms.\n\n5. **BoardReader**: This search engine specializes in indexing content from forums and message boards. You can use it to track specific keywords across various discussion platforms.\n\n6. **IFTTT (If This Then That)**: IFTTT allows you to create applets that perform specific actions when certain conditions are met. You can set up applets to receive notifications or save articles whenever keywords appear in certain contexts.\n\n7. **WebSite-Watcher**: This is a website monitoring tool that can notify you of changes to specified web pages. While it's not free, it offers affordable plans for individuals.\n\n8. **RSS Feeds**: Many websites offer RSS feeds that can be monitored using an RSS reader. You can subscribe to feeds related to your keywords to get updates whenever new content is published.\n\n9. **Screaming Frog SEO Spider**: This SEO tool allows you to crawl websites and track changes or mentions of specific keywords. While the full version is paid, there is a free version with limited features.\n\n10. **Google Advanced Search**: Using Google's advanced search operators, you can perform regular searches to find mentions of specific keywords. Although it's not automated, it can be effective for specific tracking needs.\n\nEach of these alternatives has its own strengths and may be more suitable depending on your specific needs, so it might be worthwhile to try a few and see which works best for you.",
